        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <salute>Wednesday Evn</salute>
                    <date>My dear Waterhouse</date>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>Will you be so kind as to take the trouble to send me the proper form for proposing a member (eldest son of Sir. J. Lubbock who some day will, I think, be a good &amp; active Naturalist) for the Entomological Soc.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> will you at same time tell me terms of annual payment &amp; as compounder; &amp; oblige me by getting my Proposal seconded.</p>
<p>Will you be so kind as to send me Hodgsons Pamplet on Sheep<ref target="#foot.f2"/> to Athenæum Club— you have, I think, heretofore forgotten it.—</p>
<p>Lastly you told me you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. look for chance of your having odd numbers of your Mammalia, of which I have 12, 13, 14 &amp; 15, before I order the remainder of Bailliere.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I am most truly sorry that work has stopped—</p>
<p>Ever yours | C. Darwin</p>
<p>I hope the World goes well with you.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
