        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3026.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Lubbock</ref> was elected to membership on 1 July 1850. Waterhouse was president of the Entomological Society at the time.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Hodgson 1847. CD’s annotated copy is in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL. CD had lent Waterhouse this pamphlet, see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1236.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 28 March 1849</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8192.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Waterhouse 1846–8</ref>. As a result of the outbreak of the French revolution of 1848, the publisher, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_231.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Hippolyte Baillière</ref>, was unable to continue publishing the work (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2063.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">DNB</hi></ref>). The two volumes published cover the Marsupiata and Rodentia, and both are in the Darwin Library–CUL. CD had reviewed the first volume (Marsupiata) (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 3, letter to <hi rend="italic">Annals and Magazine of Natural History</hi>, [December 1846]; <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1506.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi></ref> 1: 214–17).</note>
